            <title>[LUCENE-1158] DateTools UTC/GMT mismatch</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/LUCENE-1158</link>
                <project id="12310110" key="LUCENE">Lucene - Core</project>
                        <description>&lt;p&gt;Post from Antony Bowesman on java-user:&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;hr /&gt;

&lt;p&gt;I just noticed that although the Javadocs for Lucene 2.2 state that the dates &lt;br/&gt;
for DateTools use UTC as a timezone, they are actually using GMT.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Should either the Javadocs be corrected or the code corrected to use UTC instead.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;hr /&gt;

&lt;p&gt;I&apos;m attaching a patch that changes the javadoc and will commit it, unless someone knows a reason the javadoc is correct and the code should be changed to UTC. To my understanding, there&apos;s no significant difference between UTC and GMT.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
